Name: PULSE REPETITION FREQUENCY MEASURED IN HZ
Explanation: THE FREQUENCY AT WHICH RADAR PULSES ARE REPEATED, MEASURED IN HERTZ.

Name: PULSE REPETITION INTERVAL MEASURED IN MILLISECONDS
Explanation: THE INTERVAL BETWEEN THE START OF CONSECUTIVE RADAR PULSES, MEASURED IN MILLISECONDS.

Name: SCAN PERIOD MEASURED IN SECONDS
Explanation: THE PERIOD FOR A COMPLETE AERIAL ROTATION TO TAKE PLACE, MEASURED IN SECONDS (SPR) ACCURATE TO 1 DECIMAL PLACE.

Name: RADAR PULSE WIDTH MEASURED IN MICROSECONDS
Explanation: THE PERIOD THAT A SINGLE RADAR PULSE IS TRANSMITTED, MEASURED IN MICROSECONDS.
